  "local_port": 37982,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How does one configure TCS mail on an iPhone?",
  "response": "To configure TCS (Tata Consultancy Services) mail on an iPhone, you need to set up your TCS email account using the appropriate server settings. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to help you configure TCS mail on your iPhone:\n\n---\n\n### **Steps to Configure TCS Mail on iPhone:**\n\n1. **Open Settings:**\n   - On your iPhone, go to **Settings**.\n\n2. **Go to Mail:**\n   - Scroll down and tap on **Mail**.\n\n3. **Add Account:**\n   - Tap on **Accounts** (or **Passwords & Accounts**, depending on your iOS version).\n   - Tap on **Add Account**.\n\n4. **Choose Email Provider:**\n   - Select **Other** (since TCS mail is not listed as a default provider like Gmail or Outlook).\n\n5. **Add Mail Account:**\n   - Enter the following details:\n     - **Name:** Your full name.\n     - **Email:** Your TCS email address (e.g., `yourname@tcs.com`).\n     - **Password:** Your TCS email password.\n     - **Description:** Enter a description for the account (e.g., \"TCS Mail\").\n   - Tap **Next**.\n\n6. **Configure Incoming Mail Server (IMAP):**\n   - Ensure **IMAP** is selected at the top.\n   - **Incoming Mail Server:**\n     - **Host Name:** `imap.tcs.com`\n     - **User Name:** Your full TCS email address.\n     - **Password:** Your TCS email password.\n   - **Outgoing Mail Server (SMTP):**\n     - **Host Name:** `smtp.tcs.com`\n     - **User Name:** Your full TCS email address.\n     - **Password:** Your TCS email password.\n   - Tap **Next**.\n\n7. **Verify Settings:**\n   - Your iPhone will verify the settings. If the information is correct, it will proceed.\n\n8. **Enable Mail and Other Features:**\n   - Ensure **Mail** is enabled to access your TCS emails.\n   - You can also enable **Contacts**, **Calendars**, and **Notes** if needed.\n\n9. **Save and Finish:**\n   - Tap **Save** to complete the setup.\n\n---\n\n### **Optional - Adjust Additional Settings (if required):**\n- **SSL/TLS:** Ensure SSL is enabled for both incoming and outgoing servers.\n- **Port Settings:**\n  - Incoming Mail (IMAP): Port `993`\n  - Outgoing Mail (SMTP): Port `465` or `587`\n\n---\n\n### **Troubleshooting Tips:**\n- Ensure your TCS email account is active and the password is correct.\n- If you face issues, double-check the server settings (e.g., `imap.tcs.com` and `smtp.tcs.com`).\n- If you\u2019re using TCS\u2019s VPN or secure access, ensure you\u2019re connected to the required network.\n\n---\n\nOnce configured, your TCS mail will sync with your iPhone, and you\u2019ll be able to send and receive emails directly from the Mail app.",
